Please look at the configuration process enables video:  http://i.youku.com/ikonke</ " , if the press is still operating configuration fails,
 1. Make sure that the position of the small K WIFI signal where the normal networking or stronger signal;
 2. Make sure the WIFI password is entered correctly, and the SSID and password can not contain special characters% and ';
 3, a small K only supports 2.4G WIFI, does not support the 5G WIFI;
 4, check the router settings, if you have set a static address assignment, MAC address filtering, AP isolation may lead configuration fails;
 5, try turning off, unloading phone antivirus software;
 6, some public environment, office environment, a network administrator would do to limit the network may cause configuration to fail;
 7. After the configuration if the blue light is off, indicating that the configuration was successful. If you still can not find the device at this point in APP, please a) Check whether the phone is connected to the original WIFI WIFI signal; b) attempts between Main Menu and Device List multi-switch times; c) attempt to kill APP process, to re-enter;
 8. If the configuration fails, you can try the open key 3,4 seconds to restore the factory settings to reconfigure;"

"IOS devices with reference to Q2, after you enter configuration mode and connected to the 0K_SP3, little k client configuration page click on "direct-attached configuration", click on the direct-attached configurations can be completed;
        Android-powered devices, directly on the small K client configuration page, click the "direct-attached configuration", click on the direct-attached configurations can be completed. After configuration is complete in the "devices list" can be seen in the new device you just configured.
        Note that in direct connect mode, to connect smaller k socket, ensure that mobile phones connect to a WIFI signal from the small k socket (0K_SP3_xxxxxx, each little k "XXXXXX" will be different)."
